==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
[[File:改-clerical-han-variant.svg|128px|thumb|{{m-self|zh|改}} (in the form of 攺) from a Western-Han manuscript of the ''{{w|Etiquette and Ceremonial|Yili}}'' in the clerical script.]]

In the oracle bone script, a {{Han compound|巳|攴|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|nocap=1}}.

The interpretation linked to a child beaten or threatened by a stick in hand to indicate "correct, amend" referred to educating a child is probably folk etymology.

Since the small seal script, the phonetic component has been changed to {{och-l|己}}.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=攺}}

Related to {{och-l|革|to change}}, {{och-l|更|id=1|to change}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}).

